{"lemma":"رُسُلُ","slug":"رُسُلُ","root":"ر.س.ل","root_slug":"ر-س-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-س-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رَسُول","root":"رسل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":332},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["name","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n15484","n15491","n15492","n15493","n15494"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8F%D8%B3%D9%8F%D9%84%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"messenger; emissary; envoy; delegate"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"messenger, apostle; a prophet who is sent by God with a mission (precise definitions vary)","examples":[{"text":"رَسُولُ اللّٰهِ","english":"Messenger of God (Muhammad)"},{"text":"اَلرَّسُول","english":"the Messenger (Muhammad)"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"messenger, apostle; an apostle (leading disciple of Jesus)","examples":[{"text":"بُولُسُ الرَسُول","english":"Paul the Apostle"},{"text":"أَعْمَالُ الرُّسُل","english":"Acts of the Apostles"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"angel","examples":[{"text":"وَمَا كَانَ لِبَشَرٍ أَن يُكَلِّمَهُ اللَّهُ إِلَّا وَحْيًا أَوْ مِن وَرَاءِ حِجَابٍ أَوْ يُرْسِلَ رَسُولًا فَيُوحِيَ بِإِذْنِهِ مَا يَشَاءُ ۚ إِنَّهُ عَلِيٌّ حَكِيمٌ"}]},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Muhammad (the Messenger)","examples":[{"text":"يَا أَيُّهَا النَّاسُ قَدْ جَاءَكُمُ الرَّسُولُ بِالْحَقِّ مِن رَّبِّكُمْ فَآمِنُوا خَيْرًا لَّكُمْ","english":"(please add an English translation of this quotation)"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare أَرْسَلَ (ʔarsala, “to send”)."},"ipa":["/ra.suːl/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n15484","headword_ar":"رَسِلَ","root":"rsl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasalN","text_ar":"رَسَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasaAla","text_ar":"رَسَالَ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, easy in pace."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) ―         -b2-  Also, aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasalN","text_ar":"رَسَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, Az, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasaAlapN","text_ar":"رَسَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as above, (AZ, Az, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(hair)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became lank, not crisp;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astrsl","text_ar":"استرسل","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lank"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pendent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lank"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pendent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, Az, Msb.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yajibu","text_ar":"لَا يَجِبُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina Alb~iHoyapi","text_ar":"مِنَ البِّحْيَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gasolu maA A@sotarosala","text_ar":"غَسْلُ مَا ا@سْتَرْسَلَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The washing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of what hangs down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"descends,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the beard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] from the chin ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is not requisite,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"necessary,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"incumbent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh.)       -A2-  [Golius says, as on the authority of the KL, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasala","text_ar":"رَسَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Nuncium misit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but what I find in the KL is, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasuwlN","text_ar":"رَسُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as an inf. n., signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bringing a message"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"PygAm brdn","text_ar":"پيغام بردن"},{"kind":"text","text":") : whence it seems that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasala","text_ar":"رَسَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he brought a message."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["AZ","Az","Msb","K","S"]},{"entry_id":"n15491","headword_ar":"رَسْلٌ","root":"rsl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Easy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a pace. (M, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Easy in pace;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a he-camel: fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gentle, in pace;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a he-camel and to a she-camel: (Msb:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirosaAlN","text_ar":"مِرْسَالٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", also, applied to a she-camel, has the former of these significations; and its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraAsiylu","text_ar":"مَرَاسِيلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) or this pl. signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"active,"},{"kind":"text","text":"she-camels,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that give thee what they have to give spontaneously;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasolapN","text_ar":"رَسْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to one thereof: a she-camel is termed ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirosaAlN","text_ar":"مِرْسَالٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"as being likened to the arrow thus called. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Soft, and lax,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flaccid:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. applied to a he-camel; for it is added,] one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAqapN rasolapN AlqawaAy^imi","text_ar":"نَاقَةٌ رَسْلَةٌ القَوَايِمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A she-camel loose,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slack,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the legs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft in the joints"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thereof"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA. [See also another meaning assigned to this phrase in what follows.]) ―         -b4-  Applied to hair,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musotarosilN","text_ar":"مُسْتَرْسِلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K; in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"murosal","text_ar":"مُرْسَل"},{"kind":"text","text":";) which means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lank; not crisp:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb: [and so accord. to an explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astrsl","text_ar":"استرسل"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the S and K:]) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lank"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pendent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lank"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pendent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, Az, Msb.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasolapN","text_ar":"رَسْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasolapu AlqawAy^imi","text_ar":"رَسْلَةُ القَوايِمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [of which see an explanation in what precedes,] (L, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirosaAlN","text_ar":"مِرْسَالٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a she-camel, (M, L, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having much hair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much and long hair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon her shanks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hind legs"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY saAqiyohaA","text_ar":"فِى سَاقِيْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (M, L, TA:) but in the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasolapN","text_ar":"رَسْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muraAsilN","text_ar":"مُرَاسِلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirosaAlN","text_ar":"مِرْسَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] are explained as epithets applied to a woman, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having much and long hair upon her shanks."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b6-  Also sing. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"risaAlN","text_ar":"رِسَالٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) which signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"legs"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a camel: (AZ, S, K, TA:) so called because of their length. (AZ, TA.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muraAsilN","text_ar":"مُرَاسِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A3-  And see the paragraph here next following."}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","Msb","L","TA","AZ"]},{"entry_id":"n15492","headword_ar":"رِسْلٌ","root":"rsl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Gentleness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a deliberate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leisurely, manner of acting"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"behaving;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"risolapN","text_ar":"رِسْلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) [and perhaps ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasolN","text_ar":"رَسْلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasolapN","text_ar":"رَسْلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for] one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AifoEalo ka*aA waka*aA EalaY risolika","text_ar":"اِفْعَلْ كَذَا وَكَذَا عَلَى رِسْلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, * Msb, * CK * [but not in my MS. copy of the K nor in the copies used by SM]) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasolika","text_ar":"رَسْلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasolatika","text_ar":"رَسْلَتِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (CK, [but likewise wanting in MS. copies of the K,]) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Do thou such and such things"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at thine ease;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"act thou gently, deliberately,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leisurely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, K, *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in doing such and such things;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY hiynatika","text_ar":"عَلَى هِينَتِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) Sakhr-el-Ghei says, when despairing of his companions' overtaking him, his enemies surrounding him, and he feeling sure of slaughter, (M,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"lawo A^an~a HawoliY mino qurayomK rajolaA\n                      \n                     \n                        biyDa Alwajuwhi yaHomiluwna Aln~abolaA\n                      \n                     \n                        lamanaEuwniY najodapF A^awo risolaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Skr, M, *) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If there were around me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the family"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Kureym, men on foot, fair in the faces"},{"kind":"text","text":"(app. meant tropically),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bearing arrows, they would defend me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by violent means"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by gentle means:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Skr:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with fighting or without fighting."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) [See also a phrase cited from a trad. in what follows of this paragraph.] One says also, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAw^uwA risolapF risolapF","text_ar":"جَاوُوا رِسْلَةً رِسْلَةً","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They came company by company."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b2-  And A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft, gentle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"saying or speech. (TA.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Milk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of whatever sort it be:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or, accord. to the Towsheeh,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fresh milk."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kavura","text_ar":"كَثُرَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~isolu AlEaAma","text_ar":"الرِّسْلُ العَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Milk has become abundant this year:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the people of the desert assert that, when this is the case, dates are few; and that, when dates are abundant, milk is scarce. (TA.) ―         -b2-  It is said in a trad. [respecting the giving of the poor-rate],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_il~aA mano A^aEoTaY fiY najodatihaA warisolihaA","text_ar":"اـِلَّا مَنْ اَعْطَى فِى نَجْدَتِهَا وَرِسْلِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) which is explained in two different ways: (TA:) [J says that] it is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"risolN","text_ar":"رِسْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense first explained above; meaning straitness and plenty; i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Except him who gives when they are fat and goodly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"when it is difficult, or hard, to their owner to give them forth,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and when they are lean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a middling condition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) and A'Obeyd says the like; and that it is similar to the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAla fulaAnN ka*aA Eam~aA risolihi","text_ar":"قَالَ فُلَانٌ كَذَا عَمَّا رِسْلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one said such a thing holding it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the saying)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in light estimation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"others say that it is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"risolN","text_ar":"رِسْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying “ milk; ” which A'Obeyd disallows: IAth says that what is meant by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"njdp","text_ar":"نجدة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is straitness and drought or barrenness or dearth; and by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rsl","text_ar":"رسل"},{"kind":"text","text":", plenty, and abundance of herbage or the like; because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rsl","text_ar":"رسل"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. milk, is plentiful only in the case of abundance of herbage; so that the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"except him who gives forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"the due of God"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the case of straitness and in that of plenty."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A3-  The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"risolaAni","text_ar":"رِسْلَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a horse are The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extremities of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDudaAni","text_ar":"عَضُدَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two arms"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, K. *)"}],"source_refs":["M","Skr","S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n15493","headword_ar":"رَسَلٌ","root":"rsl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Camels:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) thus expl. by A'Obeyd, without any epithet: (M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a drove,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herd,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a distinct collection"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"number,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of camels, (S, M, * Msb, K,) and of sheep or goats, (S, K,)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1083},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to ISk"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from ten to twenty-five,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasal","text_ar":"رَسَل"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the watering-trough is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at least ten, and extending to twenty-five;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the word is masc. and fem.; (M;) and also (assumed tropical:)  of horses or horsemen; (S;) applied to (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a company"},{"kind":"text","text":"of men (Mgh, Msb) as being likened to a drove, or herd, of camels: (Msb:) and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a distinct collection"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"number"},{"kind":"text","text":"of any things: (M, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arosaAlN","text_ar":"اَرْسَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, M, Mgh, Msb, K.) A rájiz says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"yaA *aAy^idayohaA xaw~iSaA biA^arosaAlo\n                      \n                     \n                        walaA ta*uwdaAhaA *iyaAda AlD~ul~aAlo"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O ye two drivers of them, water some before others, by droves, and drive them not with the driving of those who err from the right way"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, TA:) i. e. bring near your camels some after some, and do not let them crowd upon the water-ing-trough. (TA.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='ati AlA_ibilu rasalFA","text_ar":"جَا=ءَتِ الاـِبِلُ رَسَلًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The camels came"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a drove,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"following one another."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAmb, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='ati Alxayolu A^arosaAlFA","text_ar":"جَا=ءَتِ الخَيْلُ اَرْسَالًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The horses,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"horsemen, came"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in successive distinct companies."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA'uwA A^arosaAlFA","text_ar":"جَاءُوا اَرْسَالًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They"},{"kind":"text","text":"(men)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came in successive companies."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb. [And the like is said in the Mgh and in the TA.])"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqiyrN kaviyru Alr~asali qaliylu Alr~isoli","text_ar":"وَقِيرٌ كَثِيرُ الرَّسَلِ قَلِيلُ الرِّسْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a trad. relating to a drought, is said by IKt to mean ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A collection of sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which many were sent to the pasture,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. many in number, but"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having little milk"},{"kind":"text","text":"but the more probable explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kvyr Alrsl","text_ar":"كثير الرسل"},{"kind":"text","text":"is that of El-'Odhree, who says that it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much dispersed in search of pasture:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for the trad. relates that the camels had died, notwithstanding their ability to endure drought: how then should the sheep or goats be safe, and increase so as to become numerous? (IAth, TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Animals,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beasts, having milk."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","S","TA","Mgh","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n15494","headword_ar":"رُسُلٌ","root":"rsl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young"},{"kind":"text","text":"girl,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has not worn the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"muffler,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"veil, called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xamaAr","text_ar":"خَمَار"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)       -A2-  Also a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasuwlN","text_ar":"رَسُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, M, &c.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}